goals.visualization: line chart of net generation over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is an increase or decrease in net generation over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of net generation by source?
goals.visualization: bar chart of net generation by source
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which source contributes the most to net generation.

goals.question: What is the average net generation by source?
goals.visualization: horizontal bar chart of average net generation by source
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which source has the highest average net generation.

goals.question: What is the correlation between year and net generation?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of year and net generation
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a relationship between year and net generation.

goals.question: What is the distribution of net generation?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of net generation values and identify any outliers.

code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="source", y="net_generation", data=data, ci=None, palette="muted")
    chart.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.set(xlabel='Source', ylabel='Net Generation')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].mean().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='net_generation', y='source', data=data, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['net_generation'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['net_generation'].max()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Average Net Generation')
    plt.ylabel('Source')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['net_generation'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
